5.5 The extension of the system to modal notions immediately opens the way for an account of the dual-NP reflex of the for- dative. The relevant modality here is intention. Two preliminary
remarks about the dual-NP reflex of the for-dative. First, as
far as I know, the relation R(NP , NPk) is never entailed; second, there is always a direct relation between NP and NPk* In other words, from the truth of the sentence
