cases make one somewhat uncomfortable, however. But I see no intuitive way in which to extend this notion to speaking and hear- ing. Rather, it seems as if we are dealing here with two sides
of the same linguistic coin.
57. The problem is non-trivial, since for many of the to-dative cases the role of the intention relation in the set of truth-
