Assuming that the passive transformation preposes the first NP following V, if (16) applies, then the passive rule will
generate sentences like (5) automatically, since the verb and the pronominal first object will be analyzed together
as V.
An alternative analysis assimilates the second passive
to the pseudo-passive, which allows a preposition to inter- vene between the verb and the noun phrase preposed by the
passive transformation. On this formulation, the passive is written as follows (ignoring details irrelevant to our
purpose):
17) Passive:
